12 August 2008Members of the media are invited to a briefing on government preparations for the 2010 FIFA Soccer World Cup.The briefing will be led by Transport Minister Jeff Radebe and Deputy Finance Minister Jabu Moleketi in his capacity as the chairperson of the 2010 Technical Co-ordinating Committee.The briefing will take place as follows:Date: 13 August 2008 (Wednesday) Time: 12h30 Venue: Room 153, Union Buildings, PretoriaNB: There will be a link-up to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape Town.Enquiries Tiyani Rikhotso (Pretoria) Cell: 076 034 2661Colin Cruywagen (Cape Town) Cell: 082 377 9916Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)